DynoAI Database Migrations
===========================

This directory contains Alembic database migrations for DynoAI.

Quick Start
-----------

1. Initialize the database (creates tables):
   python -c "from api.services.database import init_database; init_database()"

2. Create a new migration after model changes:
   alembic revision --autogenerate -m "Description of changes"

3. Apply all pending migrations:
   alembic upgrade head

4. Rollback the last migration:
   alembic downgrade -1

5. View migration history:
   alembic history

Configuration
-------------

The database URL is configured via:
- Environment variable: DATABASE_URL
- Default: sqlite:///./dynoai.db

Supported databases:
- SQLite (default, for development)
- PostgreSQL (for production)

Example PostgreSQL URL:
  DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:pass@localhost:5432/dynoai




